<p>The Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences awarded the 2025 prize in economic sciences to Joel Mokyr, Philippe Aghion and Peter Howitt for “having explained innovation-driven economic growth” [ft.com#1][scmp.com#5][straitstimes.com#6][dw.com#4]. The research illuminates how technological progress and innovation fuel long-run prosperity, a theme the academy and outlets emphasized in announcing the trio in Stockholm on Monday [dw.com#4][scmp.com#5]. According to reporting, one half of the prize goes to Mokyr, with the other half shared by Aghion and Howitt [thehindu.com#2]. The announcement concludes this year’s Nobel season, with Nobel festivities scheduled in Stockholm from December 6 to 12, and the other prizes having been announced last week [scmp.com#5][firstpost.com#3][straitstimes.com#6].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/vsFCKc6G6yC12-0si_44Z37q8L-XG-vUGXLO_h887Arom_rzeyQ1n4dICJT4qyc4dXpmcOUhXQOOIKfFNp5Lyvjpc_4desb9xWcgtyJUYxd1CHRmmNquwe5ebjD4OxNJS-gaGXkw9Ek5BL1WHdc-KuRzgDYXkrTJU1RS6j0k_A8-mEq4F6BBj4ZaVclOeFG9i3eZ' alt='Coverage image used for the 2025 economics Nobel announcement.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Prize split: One half of the prize goes to Joel Mokyr, while Philippe Aghion and Peter Howitt share the other half [thehindu.com#2].</li><li>Core insight: Their work explains how technological progress and innovation drive prosperity and economic growth [dw.com#4][ft.com#1].</li><li>Announcement venue: The academy announced the laureates in Stockholm on Monday [scmp.com#5][dw.com#4].</li><li>Global trio: The award went to three researchers from the United States, the United Kingdom and France [dw.com#4].</li><li>Ceremony timing: Nobel festivities are scheduled in Stockholm from December 6 to 12; other Nobel prizes were announced last week [firstpost.com#3][straitstimes.com#6].</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/9b845160-f44b-4865-94f7-1bf21e25596e'>Economics Nobel Prize awarded for explaining ‘innovation-driven’ growth</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/business/Economy/economics-nobel-to-be-shared-by-three-for-research-on-innovation-driven-economic-growth/article70157915.ece'>Economics Nobel to be shared by three for research on innovation-driven economic growth</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/nobel-prize-in-economics-awarded-to-joel-mokyr-philippe-aghion-and-peter-howitt-for-innovation-driven-growth-research-13941670.html'>Nobel Prize in Economics awarded to Joel Mokyr, Philippe Aghion and Peter Howitt for innovation-driven growth research</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/nobel-economics-prize-awarded-for-innovation-growth-theory/a-74328580'>Nobel economics prize awarded for innovation-growth theory</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3328823/mokyr-aghion-howitt-win-2025-nobel-economics-prize'>Mokyr, Aghion, Howitt win 2025 Nobel economics prize</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/mokyr-aghion-and-howitt-win-2025-nobel-economics-prize'>Mokyr, Aghion and Howitt win 2025 Nobel economics prize</a> - straitstimes.com</li></ul>